### Layer Descriptions

#### 1. (web) Layer - Next.js Routing

**Purpose:** Next.js App Router pages and API routes

**Files:**
- `page.tsx` - Page components
- `layout.tsx` - Layout wrappers
- `loading.tsx` - Loading states
- `error.tsx` - Error boundaries
- `not-found.tsx` - 404 pages
- `api/**/*.ts` - API route handlers

Define pages and layouts using Next.js conventions, handle routing through file system, API routes for backend integration, route groups for organization.

#### 2. Modules Layer

**Purpose:** Core business logic

**Files:**
- `*.module.tsx` - Module component
- `*.service.ts` - Business logic
- `*.store.ts` - Module state management
- `*.interface.ts` - Module-specific types
- `elements/` - Custom module elements

Main application features, complex page sections, orchestrate multiple widgets/features, business logic implementation.

#### 3. Widgets Layer

**Purpose:** Self-sufficient UI components

**Files:**
- `*.component.tsx` - Widget component
- `*.service.ts` - Widget logic
- `*.store.ts` - Widget state
- `elements/` - Custom widget elements

Complex reusable components, can contain internal logic, reusable across pages, independent functionality.

#### 4. Features Layer

**Purpose:** Simple reusable implementations

**Files:**
- `*.component.tsx` - Feature component
- `*.service.ts` - Feature logic
- `*.interface.ts` - Feature types

Small UI components, single-purpose functionality, feature flags, simple hooks.

#### 5. Entities Layer

**Purpose:** Business entities and data

**Files:**
- `api/*.api.ts` - API client functions
- `api/*.query.ts` - React Query hooks
- `api/*.mutation.ts` - React Mutation hooks
- `models/*.model.ts` - Data models

API integration, data models, type definitions, React Query hooks.

#### 6. Shared Layer

**Purpose:** Common utilities and components

**Files:**
- `ui/*.component.tsx` - Shared UI components
- `hooks/*.hook.tsx` - Custom hooks
- `store/*.store.ts` - Global state
- `interfaces/*.interface.ts` - Shared types
- `assets/**` - Images, icons, etc.

Reusable UI components, custom hooks, global stores, assets and icons.

#### 7. Config Layer

**Purpose:** Application configuration

**Files:**
- `env/*.ts` - Environment configuration
- `fonts/*.ts` - Font definitions
- `styles/*.css` - Global CSS

Environment variables, font configuration, global styles, app-wide settings.

#### 8. Pkg Layer

**Purpose:** External utilities and packages

Third-party integrations, custom utility packages, external API clients.

